{"issue_id": "15", "raw": "```json\n{\n  \"match\": true,\n  \"finding_index\": 58,\n  \"confidence\": 0.95\n}\n```\n\n**Explanation:** Finding [58] `PROP-6a4369e9-inv-047 (nimbus_fusaka)` directly matches the known vulnerability. Both describe:\n- A while loop in Nimbus custody group handling (`checkPeerCustody` context)\n- Infinite loop triggered when peer-reported `custody_group_count > 128`\n- The set can never reach the target size due to modular bounds (mod NUMBER_OF_CUSTODY_GROUPS = 128)\n- Results in denial of service via resource exhaustion\n\nThe finding explicitly identifies the root cause: the loop termination condition becomes unsatisfiable when the peer-controlled custody_group_count exceeds the fixed custody group limit.", "finding_ids": ["PROP-5a6a79d5-post-002", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-036", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-053", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-037", "PROP-57888860-inv-001", "PROP-57888860-post-001", "PROP-57888860-inv-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-002", "PROP-57888860-pre-003", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-005", "PROP-57888860-inv-025", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-010", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-050", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-035", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-041", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-011", "PROP-6a4369e9-post-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-036", "PROP-57888860-asm-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-026", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-027", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-013", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-001", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-005", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-039", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-030", "PROP-57888860-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-008", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-023", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-012", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-013", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-043", "PROP-6a