{"issue_id": "40", "raw": "```json\n{\n  \"match\": true,\n  \"finding_index\": 25,\n  \"confidence\": 0.95\n}\n```\n\nFinding [25] (PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-018, lighthouse_fusaka) directly describes this vulnerability:\n\n> \"Post-Fulu spec requires get_beacon_proposer_index to return proposer_lookahead[slot % SLOTS_PER_EPOCH]. All three gossip verification paths (data_column L688, blob L536, block L991) call get_beacon_proposer_indices instead, which always recomputes from active validators without reading proposer_look...\"\n\nThis matches the known vulnerability: the code calls `get_beacon_proposer_indices` (which recomputes from scratch) instead of reading from the cached `proposer_lookahead` array, causing potential mismatches when validator state changes occur.", "finding_ids": ["PROP-5a6a79d5-post-002", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-036", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-053", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-037", "PROP-57888860-inv-001", "PROP-57888860-post-001", "PROP-57888860-inv-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-002", "PROP-57888860-pre-003", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-005", "PROP-57888860-inv-025", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-010", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-050", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-035", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-041", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-011", "PROP-6a4369e9-post-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-036", "PROP-57888860-asm-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-026", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-027", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-013", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-001", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-005", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-039", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-030", "PROP-57888860-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-008", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-023", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-012", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-013", "PROP-