{"issue_id": "176", "raw": "```json\n{\n  \"match\": true,\n  \"finding_index\": 56,\n  \"confidence\": 0.88\n}\n```\n\nFinding [56] directly matches the known vulnerability. Both describe:\n- **Nethermind** blob transaction handling\n- **Missing length-equality enforcement** between two arrays (`blobVersionedHashes` and `blobs.Blobs`)\n- **Mismatched loop bounds** creating potential unguarded indexing\n- The consequence of array length mismatch causing validation bypass or access errors\n\nThe finding specifically states that `ValidateHashes` uses two different loop bounds without asserting length equality between the arrays, which aligns perfectly with the known vulnerability's description of \"missing length-equality enforcement combined with...unguarded indexing\" affecting blob transaction validation during payload assembly.", "finding_ids": ["PROP-5a6a79d5-post-002", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-036", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-053", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-037", "PROP-57888860-inv-001", "PROP-57888860-post-001", "PROP-57888860-inv-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-002", "PROP-57888860-pre-003", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-005", "PROP-57888860-inv-025", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-010", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-050", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-035", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-041", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-011", "PROP-6a4369e9-post-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-036", "PROP-57888860-asm-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-026", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-027", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-013", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-001", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-005", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-039", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-030", "PROP-57888860-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-008", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-023", "PROP-56ad1e