{"issue_id": "190", "raw": "```json\n{\n  \"match\": true,\n  \"finding_index\": 73,\n  \"confidence\": 0.98\n}\n```\n\n**Finding [73]** directly matches the known vulnerability. It explicitly identifies that Prysm's cache key for `verify_data_column_sidecar_inclusion_proof` omits `KzgCommitments`, including only the inclusion proof and header hash. This allows two data columns with identical proofs/headers but different commitments to produce the same cache key, causing the second to skip verification—exactly as described in Issue #190.", "finding_ids": ["PROP-5a6a79d5-post-002", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-036", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-053", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-037", "PROP-57888860-inv-001", "PROP-57888860-post-001", "PROP-57888860-inv-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-002", "PROP-57888860-pre-003", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-005", "PROP-57888860-inv-025", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-010", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-050", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-035", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-041", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-011", "PROP-6a4369e9-post-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-036", "PROP-57888860-asm-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-026", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-027", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-013", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-001", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-005", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-039", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-030", "PROP-57888860-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-008", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-023", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-012", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-013", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-043", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-037", "PROP-6a4369e9-post-002", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-008", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-027", "PROP-1ada093f-inv-041", "PROP-aa9e39fd-inv-008", "PROP-aa9e39fd-inv-009", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-059", "PROP-aa9