{"issue_id": "203", "raw": "```json\n{\n  \"match\": true,\n  \"finding_index\": 5,\n  \"confidence\": 0.85\n}\n```\n\n**Finding [5]** — PROP-57888860-inv-001 (c_kzg_4844_fusaka) — directly detects a flaw in the Fiat-Shamir challenge computation of `verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch`: the challenge hash uses the original `commitments_bytes` array (with duplicates) instead of the deduplicated `unique_commitments` array, enabling malleability attacks. This is characteristic of weak Fiat-Shamir transformation — the challenge input is computed incorrectly, undermining the proof's security.\n\nFinding [7] (PROP-57888860-inv-003) describes the same root cause with additional detail about line 877 passing the wrong array to `compute_verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_challenge`.", "finding_ids": ["PROP-5a6a79d5-post-002", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-036", "PROP-5a6a79d5-inv-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-053", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-037", "PROP-57888860-inv-001", "PROP-57888860-post-001", "PROP-57888860-inv-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-002", "PROP-57888860-pre-003", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-005", "PROP-57888860-inv-025", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-008", "PROP-57888860-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-010", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-050", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-035", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-041", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-018", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-011", "PROP-6a4369e9-post-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-036", "PROP-57888860-asm-003", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-026", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-027", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-013", "PROP-6a4369e9-asm-001", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-pre-005", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-029", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-039", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-030", "PROP-57888860-inv-028", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-008", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-009", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-014", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-023", "PROP-56ad1eb2-inv-032", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-012", "PROP-6a4369e9-inv-013", "PROP-6a4